elements.2211.03051_80498cdd8fe741db53837d89500b7: Zebrafish are a common model organism used to identify new disease therapeutics
elements.2211.03051_88a7c3696223fe1dd84c5485bd8f1: High-throughput drug screens can be performed on larval zebrafish in multi-well plates by observing changes in behaviour following a treatment
elements.2211.03051_a3333cad80e874edf9ea00f3d58ff: Analysis of this behaviour can be difficult, however, due to the high dimensionality of the data obtained
elements.2211.03051_711cdf1b5ff8ee21f3c9877a9d064: Statistical analysis of individual statistics (such as the distance travelled) is generally not powerful enough to detect meaningful differences between treatment groups
elements.2211.03051_49dabd3f6340c6280dc31dc8a7bd4: Here, we propose a method for classifying zebrafish models of Parkinson's disease by genotype at 5 days old
elements.2211.03051_4159e7dbdd225db63935e12abb526: Using a set of 2D behavioural features, we train a multi-layer perceptron neural network
elements.2211.03051_03c941f25a5834c8c479deecfd737: We further show that the use of integrated gradients can give insight into the impact of each behaviour feature on genotype classifications by the model
elements.2211.03051_43496c24ff4264670e7e08ad15e91: In this way, we provide a novel pipeline for classifying zebrafish larvae, beginning with feature preparation and ending with an impact analysis of said features.
elements.2211.03051_670812949097af7b8390fbdb91da2: Zebrafish are commonly used as model organisms of disease due to their genetic tractability and high reproductive capabilities
elements.2211.03051_b299a8777af850fbf7bca8d17b9f1: To identify new therapeutics for disease treatment and management, high-throughput drug screens can be performed on larval zebrafish in multi-well plates, where some phenotypic response to the treatment is measured
elements.2211.03051_8e38ffab639a8a6332311bece17ff: Finding a measurable response can be a challenge, however, which is what we aimed to interrogate here.
elements.2211.03051_8d8b3d51430cfb422544a7c05fa6e: The behaviour of zebrafish larvae can be analysed by tracking their movement in a controlled environment and extracting features such as the distance travelled, velocity of movement, or current position in the well
elements.2211.03051_0850d9a863cd9fba6065c6b9612d4: However, analysis of this data is complex as it is the combination of these features that defines behaviour.
elements.2211.03051_66022d41544cd78676a522e126a6e: The application of machine learning (ML) in biology for classifying model organisms, including zebrafish, is not a new idea in any account
elements.2211.03051_7099a318dff9f58f991efbfbb947a: Deep convolutional neural networks trained on coloured images of zebrafish are able to classify them by sex
elements.2211.03051_af759d9f231ebea3e8fe01c6c02cc: The authors did not limit their work to neural networks, however, as they show that sex can also be determined by modelling caudal fin correlation via linear discrimination using support vector machines (SVMs), another well-known supervised learning method
elements.2211.03051_45be82a53e4eb64e3e16b8a428325: The effectiveness of these approaches are unfortunately unclear due to missing explanation of their method for model training and evaluation.
elements.2211.03051_3ccafbcb86362aafb55ceff36c9e5: In this paper, we present a non-linear ML classifier that can predict the genotype of larval zebrafish models of Parkinson's disease (mutation in
elements.2211.03051_55f297f895f758a81d6e872a964f6: , known to cause juvenile-onset PD in humans) with an average of 84
elements.2211.03051_cbc8a359e3b287d4376bf794fdcd4: validation accuracy based on 2D behavioural features
elements.2211.03051_be53ec7998d00a05551415b4d1544: This classifier could potentially be used to indicate whether a mutant larva is displaying a
elements.2211.03051_8b0f262208f97a00ae65c7e0fb0bb: mutant" behavioural phenotype following a certain treatment
elements.2211.03051_73dd13ead67b57c6052d218a621a0: We then analyse the impact of behavioural features by calculating the integrated gradients of our models to inform us of the distinguishing features of the genotypes.
elements.2211.03051_443af07b571d0c3d6fc0d4f69fa7b: Our proposed network architecture has an input layer of 41 dimensions, three hidden layers of
elements.2211.03051_65f5031aef0bd1e0d993f54eb25e3: dimensions, and an output layer of two dimensions
elements.2211.03051_5cbd2166c733fa695358cfcc66f53: We chose an output size of two, even though we are solving a binary classification problem, to allow for the simple addition of another genotype for classification (heterozygous)
elements.2211.03051_6ff76c1ba06c20852e71210fb01cc: The optimal dimension of the hidden layers is decided after evaluating our experiments as discussed in the next section
elements.2211.03051_e98aebf8fb12fa0fc4d19ea5e652f: The architecture is visualised in Figure
elements.2211.03051_6c55b22a482293966735c39b54910: Random initialisation of a neural network has been shown to lead to slower convergence and toward poorer local minima
elements.2211.03051_b37c8c2c3df740bab4b50efa23aa1: Xavier initialisation is a popular arrow in the quiver of deep neural network (NN) researchers as it decreases the probability of encountering the vanishing/exploding gradients problem during training
elements.2211.03051_9b96147c5d314ec6cb1ba1af71a23: However, this method is based on the assumption that are linear
elements.2211.03051_c76dfba9e6ba3b63effa216a2cdad: This assumption is invalid for the ReLU activation function used in our proposed architecture
elements.2211.03051_e1f2be87131704942f7de45b23cc4: . proposed a new initialisation strategy for ReLU-activated networks
elements.2211.03051_8f47b826940cf22a1c368f87afa7c: sets the network weights randomly from a normal distribution, as in Xavier initialisation, but with a variance of:
elements.2211.03051_97903c0dba21b4626038dddf94fe0: in order to reduce the probability of the dying neuron problem.
elements.2211.03051_cce6d850d5718f02d98f9a13a805d: Batch size is an important contributor to the generalisation ability of a network
elements.2211.03051_8cd0cb9c27cf2a0d6d9888bedc93a: When employing stochastic gradient descent as a learning strategy, it is necessary to ensure that the batch size is not too large so as to not reduce the gradient noise
elements.2211.03051_e71dbf481173d9bcde2f8579dc8c1: Fluctuation in gradient is sometimes required to escape a poor local minima, thus reduction of this ability can be detrimental
elements.2211.03051_8e1a51a773343254496b5aa701549: proved helpful for our network to reach good minima in an adequate amount of epochs
elements.2211.03051_fc609cb82e4b1f9bf126b23fc4703: A significant contribution to the field in terms of improving the generalisation of a network is Dropout
elements.2211.03051_13ab3679b41f8557f93352f50db66: The proposed idea is to randomly drop perceptrons and their connections from the network during training
elements.2211.03051_57f06718e288e9014fceaac63b3f4: Although simple it is extremely effective and has seen massive adoption to network architectures
elements.2211.03051_e87a4137a49a3b379b03185bea499: By randomly inhibiting the network it prevents units from co-adapting too much
elements.2211.03051_69d40224123187988c7bf4d603150: Metaphorically speaking, it prevents the network from memorising the answers to the test since it is easier than studying the concepts
elements.2211.03051_0e72b35a0f7f9d8028fb972bd993d: We found that inciting a dropout (
elements.2211.03051_ea524d829f3048e45b6900f4f4476: ) after the first and second layers of our network was ideal for achieving greater generalisation.
elements.2211.03051_1fef862038b896c3af9e233240416: Understanding the flow of information through NNs is a challenging problem that has recently gained increased attention
elements.2211.03051_c2e1b005f20a20fa8ee31215feb2b: Being able to analyse the impact of input features on outputs allow further analysis and selection of features for obtaining better results
elements.2211.03051_5b2812d63b29671d4de1e89469765: A simple manner of evaluating the importance of features given by a network can be by analysing the input gradients, that is, the gradients between the input layer and the first hidden layer
elements.2211.03051_2a8d1f75f95687da4467154abc35f: But this has a clear limitation of only representing a small portion of the network, akin to looking at it through a peep hole
elements.2211.03051_e208e527fc8457f1c80f82d8921b2: We make use of a method that satisfies two fundamental axoims of attribution -
elements.2211.03051_40cce6c5327ffd57a79255fb61fbc: In simpler words, a lack of sensitivity causes gradients to focus on irrelevant features and networks that produce the same outputs, given the same input data, should always have the same attributions
elements.2211.03051_80a9e9ba2b1b516a50edc82db234a: Sundararajan et al. show that most methods do not satisfy these axioms and proposed a new method
elements.2211.03051_8af05c69d8e2cbc7aee3972eeaada: Integrated gradients postulates an additional axiom called
elements.2211.03051_9057859d5764508de06ba4b9797d1: , the attributions should add up to the difference between the output of a network and a baseline
elements.2211.03051_b5802af4f77821e0bbe9bc36be4ae: It is suggested that the baseline be chosen such that its prediction is near zero
elements.2211.03051_4daa8dfc5ffe4e57b92707fed200b: The proposed technique can be applied to a range of network architectures, including ours.
elements.2211.03051_d3d8ff77f5d6da3bc02b8da16c81b: We designed a lightweight neural network for classifying wildtype and mutant genotypes
elements.2211.03051_f7a7dc9436f21f2925f140278a84e: An important design choice was for the network to be able to be trained using a portable laptop, in our case, an M1 Macbook Pro
elements.2211.03051_5bc2ab89f3bdf8e9aabe86303b87e: This was accomplished by only having a hidden depth of three layers that are fully connected
elements.2211.03051_03e2fd62b73d34a0f9f091d7e30c9: A sufficiently wide neural network with just a single hidden layer can approximate any (reasonable) function given sufficient training data, although increasing the hypothesis space requires an exponential increase in width
elements.2211.03051_b522d204ba39655423e64fd784090: Our hypothesis space is sufficiently small where three layers is adequate to approximate our ideal function
elements.2211.03051_f673d1b8e405a3eee0bd2268d8906: The output of the final layer in the NN is passes through a sigmoid function to produce a probability distribution
elements.2211.03051_c099f07ecff447bd353ec70831e60: A logistic loss (binary cross entropy) with one-hot encoded labels is used to calculate the error between the predicted distribution and the true distribution
elements.2211.03051_06481beb915e5efd595ed2154e26f: The loss is backpropagated via stochastic gradient descent (SGD)
elements.2211.03051_7e6183ea6e28f21d15fdada7f3698: where, paired with the non-linear activation function ReLU, we are able to reliably find the global minima of the training loss
elements.2211.03051_f065d30b6f4345f7670dad4c70a73: Adding momentum to SGD has also been shown to be helpful in traversing sub-optimal local minima
elements.2211.03051_cc3d0c2f88afd44c9e1e3cfa287ce: was chosen in combination with a momentum of
elements.2211.03051_a79188f4b37957171cc21a407ad32: and proved to be near optimal for our network training.

elements.2211.03051_3ce0598185e2998f17d9b2a68264a: genotypes were generated by heterozygous incross of two parent pairs
